You are an expert in React, TypeScript, Vite, and Material UI (MUI).

## Project Context
This is a workout tracking application built with React 18, TypeScript, Vite 5, and MUI v6. Data is persisted to localStorage using custom hooks.

## Code Style

### TypeScript
- Use TypeScript strict mode conventions
- Prefer interfaces for object shapes, type aliases for unions
- Always type function parameters and return values explicitly
- Import types from `src/types.ts` for domain entities

### React
- Use functional components exclusively
- Use named exports for all components except App.tsx
- Prefer hooks for state and side effects
- Keep components focused - extract logic to custom hooks when reusable

### MUI Styling
- Use the `sx` prop for all component styling
- Reference theme values via the sx prop (e.g., `bgcolor: 'background.default'`)
- Never use inline styles or separate CSS files
- Theme customizations belong in `src/theme.ts`

### State Management
- Use existing custom hooks from `src/hooks/` for domain state
- Use `useLocalStorage` hook for persisted state
- Avoid prop drilling - create new hooks if needed
- No external state management libraries

## File Organization
- Pages go in `src/pages/` - one component per route
- Reusable components go in `src/components/{Feature}/`
- Custom hooks go in `src/hooks/` with `use` prefix
- Shared types go in `src/types.ts`

## When Writing Code
- Follow existing patterns in the codebase
- Use existing hooks rather than creating new localStorage logic
- Keep bundle size in mind - avoid adding new dependencies without justification
- Ensure new code works on mobile viewports (this is a mobile-first app)

## Domain Knowledge
- Exercise categories: 'machine', 'free_weight', 'bodyweight'
- WorkoutSet contains reps (number) and weight (number)
- PersonalRecord tracks max weight per rep count
- Workouts have startTime and endTime (ISO strings) for duration tracking
- WorkoutTemplates save exercise configurations for quick workout starts
- TemplateExercise stores exerciseId with default sets, reps, and weight

## Common Tasks
- Adding a new page: Create in `src/pages/`, add route in `App.tsx`, add nav item in `BottomNav.tsx`
- Adding a new exercise field: Update `Exercise` interface in `types.ts`, update `defaultExercises.ts`
- Adding new workout data: Extend relevant interfaces in `types.ts`, update hooks as needed
